cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CS, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

This paper primarily focuses on the social aspects of Facebook usage and the demographic disparities in its adoption and use. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses data analysis and statistical methods to study Facebook usage, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry and Topology) or cs.CS (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses the nuances of demographic differentials in the adoption and use of digital technologies, which could be relevant to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
